400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Everything-Everything.-Credit-Steve-Gullick-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Everything-Everything.-Credit-Steve-Gullick-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Everything-Everything.-Credit-Steve-Gullick-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Everything-Everything.-Credit-Steve-Gullick-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/everything-everything">Everything Everything</a>分享了他们即将发行的第七张专辑中的世界末日新歌“The Mad Stone”。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/everything-everything-on-their-apocalyptic-new-album-i-cant-see-much-good-in-the-future-3525605">他们的世界末日新专辑中的一切一切：“我看不到未来有多少美好的事情”</a></strong></li></ul><p> 《The Mad Stone》是乐队专辑《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/everything-everything-announce-new-album-mountainhead-and-2024-uk-tour-buy-tickets-preorder-3522070">Mountainhead</a> 》中发行的第二首单曲。它是继主打单曲“ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/everything-everything-share-new-single-cold-reactor-and-more-details-of-album-mountainhead-3523541">Cold Reactor</a> ”之后的。新曲目由 Alex Robertshaw 和 Tom AD Fuller 制作，他们的共同笔名是 Kaines &amp; Tom AD。</p><p>在新闻稿中谈到这首歌时，Everything Everything 主唱乔纳森·希格斯 (Johnathan Higgs) 表示：“这首歌阐述了专辑的宏大叙事，其中一个社会正在永远建造一座巨大的山脉，代价是生活在由此产生的巨大洞中（采石场）。 ）”。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="一切一切 - 疯狂的石头（视觉效果）" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/TEb9rDs0x9Q?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>他继续说道：“亚历克斯创作了管弦乐伴奏，我们录制了很多团体声乐，以赋予它一种市政合唱的声音。”</p><p> 《Mountainhead》将于 3 月 1 日发行，可<a href="https://ee.lnk.to/MountainheadPR" target="_blank" rel="noopener">在此处</a>预存/预订。</p><p>这张专辑以“Mountainhead”的概念为中心，新闻材料将其描述为“一个另类社会，在这个社会中，处于社会底层的人们被迫不懈地工作，以保持山顶精英的地位”。</p><p>希格斯补充了这个概念：“在另一个世界，社会建造了一座巨大的山。为了让山变得更大，他们必须让他们居住的洞越来越深。一切社会都是围绕山而建立的，山地宗教主导着一切思想。传说山顶有一面巨大的镜子，不断映照出自我的影像，而坑底则有一条巨大的金蛇，这是所有信徒最原始的恐惧。</p><p> “‘山头’是指相信山必须生长的人，无论付出什么代价，无论住在大坑里有多么可怕。山越高，洞就越深。” </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cztu8cBMgRY/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding: 19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block; height:50px; margin:0 auto 12px; width:50px;"><svg width="50px" height="50px" viewBox="0 0 60 60" version="1.1" xmlns="https://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="https://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><g transform="translate(-511.000000, -20.000000)" fill="#000000"><g><path d="M556.869,30.41 C554.814,30.41 553.148,32.076 553.148,34.131 C553.148,36.186 554.814,37.852 556.869,37.852 C558.924,37.852 560.59,36.186 560.59,34.131 C560.59,32.076 558.924,30.41 556.869,30.41 M541,60.657 C535.114,60.657 530.342,55.887 530.342,50 C530.342,44.114 535.114,39.342 541,39.342 C546.887,39.342 551.658,44.114 551.658,50 C551.658,55.887 546.887,60.657 541,60.657 M541,33.886 C532.1,33.886 524.886,41.1 524.886,50 C524.886,58.899 532.1,66.113 541,66.113 C549.9,66.113 557.115,58.899 557.11